00:41.374 --> 00:44.449
Word of caution,
I would refrain from sharing popcorn

00:44.574 --> 00:46.201
with the gentleman to your left

00:46.326 --> 00:49.504
as I saw him cut a hole
in the bottom of his bucket.

00:49.629 --> 00:50.422
He's kidding.

00:50.547 --> 00:51.847
Popcorn?

00:54.034 --> 00:56.578
Hello.
I'm Steve Smith.

00:56.703 --> 00:57.986
I'm sitting right over there.

01:01.508 --> 01:02.771
What?

01:02.937 --> 01:05.570
In the past, I have personally
made ironclad cases

01:05.695 --> 01:08.807
as to why I am the perfect
candidate to own a dog.

01:08.932 --> 01:13.178
I am an American boy and I both
crave and offer companionship.

01:13.303 --> 01:15.146
But tonight, I'm calling on
other folks

01:15.271 --> 01:16.514
to help me make my case.

01:16.639 --> 01:18.233
This is my best friend, Snot.

01:18.358 --> 01:21.853
I'm Snot Lonstein
and this is my dog Dreidel.

01:21.978 --> 01:25.056
We get a lot of comments
when I walk him.

01:25.181 --> 01:28.076
"Hey, who's walking who?"
is one I particularly enjoy.

01:28.201 --> 01:30.382
That's good fun.

01:30.548 --> 01:31.425
That's enough!

01:31.591 --> 01:33.481
Steve, I've told you over and over,

01:33.606 --> 01:35.967
I will never allow anyone in
this house to get a dog!

01:36.092 --> 01:38.181
Ever!

01:38.347 --> 01:39.521
I agree with Stan.

01:39.646 --> 01:41.226
I'm the only pet this house needs.

01:41.392 --> 01:42.644
What about me?

01:42.810 --> 01:45.230
You can't be a pet unless
someone loves you.

01:52.028 --> 01:54.602
Stan, don't you think
you were a little harsh

01:54.727 --> 01:55.804
with Steve in there?

01:55.929 --> 01:58.456
I'm tired of his constant pleas
for a dog.

01:58.581 --> 02:00.692
It's, "Dog, dog, dog," all day long.

02:00.817 --> 02:02.160
You think you can get something

02:02.285 --> 02:03.540
just by saying it enough?

02:03.787 --> 02:05.530
If that were true,
all I'd be saying is

02:05.655 --> 02:09.199
"Jane Seymour from behind."
Just "Jane Seymour from behind,

02:09.324 --> 02:12.787
Jane Seymour from behind,"
over and over.

02:12.912 --> 02:14.546
Jane Seymour from behind?

02:17.317 --> 02:18.460
Stan, have you considered

02:18.585 --> 02:22.530
that maybe you won't let
Steve have a dog

02:22.655 --> 02:24.366
because of a deeper issue?

02:24.491 --> 02:26.217
You know damn well why!

02:28.845 --> 02:32.694
<i>When I was a boy,
I had a dog named Freddy.</i>

02:32.860 --> 02:35.655
<i>He was my best friend.</i>

02:35.821 --> 02:37.699
<i>But right after my dad left us,</i>

02:37.865 --> 02:39.798
<i>my mom said Freddy was diagnosed</i>

02:39.923 --> 02:43.914
<i>with what is now known
as "Air Bud" disease.</i>

02:44.080 --> 02:47.417
<i>She told me the humane thing
to do was to put Freddy down.</i>

02:47.583 --> 02:50.962
Nooo...

02:51.128 --> 02:53.385
My mom said to.

02:57.009 --> 03:00.225
Please accept your fate with dignity.

03:03.463 --> 03:05.724
<i>Turns out Freddy wasn't even sick.</i>

03:05.849 --> 03:08.438
<i>They just didn't allow dogs at
our new apartment building.</i>

03:08.604 --> 03:11.012
<i>And because of that super sad story,</i>

03:11.137 --> 03:12.897
<i>I will never have a dog in my home.</i>

03:13.022 --> 03:14.399
<i>It's such a sad story</i>

03:14.524 --> 03:16.446
<i>that I won't even undercut it
with a joke.</i>

03:16.612 --> 03:19.354
<i>I'm just gonna let it end sad.</i>

03:20.647 --> 03:21.923
Are you sure you don't want

03:22.048 --> 03:23.725
to come up with some
joke to end that?

03:23.850 --> 03:25.693
Nope.
Keeping it sad.

03:25.818 --> 03:27.362
Stan, we had a dog already.

03:27.487 --> 03:28.792
I don't think so.

03:28.958 --> 03:30.365
We did.

03:30.490 --> 03:32.767
Five years ago you got Steve
an old dog

03:32.892 --> 03:34.736
that peed dust, and you killed it.

03:34.861 --> 03:37.572
We also had another dog named Fussy

03:37.697 --> 03:39.719
that you didn't like or something.

03:39.885 --> 03:41.676
Francine, those were
obviously dreams.

03:41.801 --> 03:44.336
I refuse to discuss
your dreams in the daytime.

03:48.644 --> 03:50.168
Hey, Roger, what's...?

03:50.293 --> 03:51.419
Where the hell have you been?!

03:51.544 --> 03:52.703
You are not going to believe

03:52.828 --> 03:54.025
what's going on in this house.

03:54.191 --> 03:55.690
Things are really going
to pot around here.

03:55.815 --> 03:57.342
Great. It's locked.

03:57.467 --> 03:58.780
I forgot my key.

03:58.946 --> 04:00.411
Of course you never gave me a key.

04:00.536 --> 04:02.117
That kinda bothers me,
but that's not important.

04:02.283 --> 04:04.132
What is important is
what's going on around here!

04:04.257 --> 04:05.934
You're gonna see, buddy,
oh, you are gonna see!

04:06.059 --> 04:07.152
This is great.

04:07.277 --> 04:08.386
Suddenly security's
real tight around here.

04:08.511 --> 04:09.604
You are just gonna lose it

04:09.729 --> 04:11.626
when you see what's
going on in your house!

04:11.792 --> 04:13.057
You are really gonna blow your stack!

04:13.182 --> 04:15.160
The worst part of it
is the disrespect to you,

04:15.285 --> 04:16.494
They are castrating you,
quite frankly.

04:16.619 --> 04:17.966
I'm sorry, but that's
what they're doing.

04:18.132 --> 04:19.147
They are cutting off your nads,

04:19.272 --> 04:20.582
period, end of story.

04:20.707 --> 04:22.929
Oh, you're gonna see it so soon!

04:23.095 --> 04:23.722
Look!

04:26.246 --> 04:27.172
It's sloppy!

04:27.297 --> 04:28.289
It's so wet!

04:28.414 --> 04:30.592
Oh, I love you, too!

04:30.717 --> 04:31.938
What in the hell is that?

04:32.104 --> 04:34.316
It's my new dog, Kisses!

04:35.649 --> 04:39.267
I said no dogs!

04:39.392 --> 04:41.031
Oh, this is good for Steve.

04:41.197 --> 04:44.522
And it'll be good for you
to love a dog again.

04:44.647 --> 04:48.914
I bet Freddy is smiling down
from doggie heaven right now.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.762
I hope he is.

04:50.887 --> 04:52.997
I hope he's up there,
living in a lake house,

04:53.122 --> 04:54.866
driving a kickass speedboat,

04:54.991 --> 04:56.880
eating the foamy grass
he just threw up.

04:57.046 --> 05:00.405
Let Steve keep Kisses, Stan.

05:00.530 --> 05:03.208
Fine. But I won't have
anything to do with that dog.

05:03.333 --> 05:05.243
If he buys a table
at a charity event,

05:05.368 --> 05:07.035
I won't sit at it.

05:09.305 --> 05:10.415
I'm mad at you.

05:10.540 --> 05:13.241
You are consistently
a problem for me.

